<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BITES: FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES PERRY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In listing the James Beard Award winners May 2, we failed to mention two 
Californians who won in broadcasting categories: Diane Worthington for Best 
Radio Show ("The California Cook," KABC) and Martin Yan for Best TV Show ("Yan 
Can Cook," PBS). We weren't going to mention this, but while we're up, The 
Times' Food Section also achieved some notice. Former Food Editor Ruth Reichl 
won for Best News Feature ("How to Buy Fresh Fish") and Times Staff Writer 
Daniel P. Puzo was runner-up for Food Reporting. CHARLES PERRY 
</P>
