<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALESTINIAN POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pictures of large crowds of Palestinians joyously welcoming the new 
Palestinian police force to Gaza and Jericho (May 13) as conquering heroes 
after 27 years of Israeli rule are nice but I wonder if the Palestinians may be 
celebrating too soon. Now comes the task of establishing a government and 
stable economic and strategic relationships with Israel and their neighbors. 
</P>
<P>
 I hope that soon the Palestinians and their leadership will realize that 
celebrations are nice, but the proof is in what they are able to accomplish in 
the next weeks and months. Talk is cheap if all the Palestinians gain is 
sovereignty over an ungovernable territory. 
</P>
<P>
 It bodes well for Israel to be rid of the responsibility of governing Gaza. It 
also bodes well for Israel to see a stable government and a sense of prosperity 
come to the citizens of Gaza and Jericho. 
</P>
<P>
 STEVE LIPMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 
</P>
