BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sony Launches Computer Division: Sony Corp. of America said it launched the 
new division to market computer hardware and software in the United States.Sony 
Computer Entertainment of America will focus on the company's new CD-based home 
video game system, PlayStation, and will be responsible for third-party video 
game software licensing. Stephen Race has been appointed executive vice 
president and general manager of the new division, the company said. The 
PlayStation incorporates advanced graphics and sound into a computer system. It 
is scheduled to be released in Japan by the end of 1994 and in the United 
States in 1995. 
