<HEADLINE>
<P>
A VERY BERRY OXNARD WEEKEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard claims to harvest 23% of California's strawberries, so it's fitting 
that the town folk will celebrate their harvest with the annual California 
Strawberry Festival this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Strawberry delights range from crepes and blintzes to chocolate-dipped berries 
and strawberry cheesecake on a stick.For strawberry lovers who can't shove 
enough of 'em down their throats, there are competitions such as the Strawberry 
Shortcake Eating Contest. 
</P>
<P>
 If you start to see too much red, there are also three stages full of 
performers, including Big Mountain, Three Dog Night, Doug Kershaw and the 
Temptations, along with children's entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 For those who overload on calories, there's a 10K race and non-competitive 
two-mile Family Dash at 8 a.m. Sunday. The festival is 10 a.m.-6:30 p.m. 
Saturday-Sunday at Strawberry Meadows of College Park, 3250 S. Rose Ave. $5; 
children 2-12 and seniors, $3. Information: (805) 444-5544. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
