WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; SEWER REPLACEMENT DELAYED A WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A weeklong sewer-replacement project that was scheduled to begin this week and 
close the downtown portion of Ojai Avenue has been delayed, officials with the 
project's contractor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting at 7 a.m. Monday, Ojai Avenue will be closed between Montgomery and 
Ventura streets and traffic detoured around the Ojai Arcade and adjacent 
businesses by Matilija and Aliso streets. 
</P>
<P>
 The contractor, Dorfman Construction, postponed the sewer project for a week 
to notify businesses that deliver goods to downtown Ojai of the road closure. 
</P>
<P>
 "After talking with the city and the fact that Ojai Avenue is a state highway, 
we felt an obligation to the delivery services," said Maurya Foy, project 
coordinator for Dorfman Construction. 
</P>
<P>
 The road is expected to be closed a week.  
</P>
<P>
 The excavation is part of the Ojai Valley Sanitation District's 
sewer-replacement project that started in August, 1993, and is expected to be 
completed by June 30. TRACY WILSON 
