<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION TENNIS PLAYOFFS; DOUBLES ARE DIFFERENCE IN MISSION VIEJO 
VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Josh Fair and Kuong Tran swept at No. 2 doubles to help Mission Viejo defeat 
Villa Park, 12 2/3-8 1/3, in a first-round Division I boys' tennis match 
Wednesday at Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 Fair and Tran, who won their sets, 6-0, 6-2, 6-2, and Fernando Machuca and 
Christian Fernandez at No. 3 doubles, pulled out the victory after the Diablos 
lost more than half of their singles sets and their No. 1 doubles team lost its 
first set. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo (10-8) advances to the second round, where it will play 
fourth-seeded Corona del Mar today. Villa Park finished the season 13-6. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Division I first-round matches: 
</P>
<P>
