Tyler Stonebreaker swept its sets, 6-0, 6-1, 6-0, for Corona del Mar (19-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 15 1/3, Canyon 5 2/3 -- Erik Lundblad won at No. 1 singles, 6-0, 
6-1, 2-6, for Dana Hills (20-0), which will meet Woodbridge in the next round. 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 14 2/3, El Toro 6 1/3 -- No. 3 singles player Roger Chang overcame a 
bout with the flu and posted a 6-1, 6-2, 6-0 sweep for Foothill (20-1). 
Teammate Jack Huang also swept at No. 1 singles for the Knights, which faces 
University today in the second round. 
</P>
