<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NOTES: NELSON, AKAU ON NAIA SCHOLAR LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carrie Nelson, an outfielder at Southern California College, and Shannon Akau, 
a Buena Park High graduate pitching for Hawaii Pacific, have been named NAIA 
softball All-American scholar-athletes, the organization announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson, a junior from Broomfield, Colo., is carrying a 3.62 grade-point 
average in mathematics.Akau, a senior, has a 3.65 average in humanities. 
</P>
<P>
 The award honors juniors and seniors with a cumulative GPA of at least 3.50 on 
a 4.0 scale. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Dave McLeish, Southern California College men's soccer coach, has announced 
several player signings. They are: 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Villar, a junior transfer midfielder who played at Tustin High and 
Orange Coast College; Brian Hurley, a forward from El Dorado High; Brian 
McDuffie, a fullback from Rim of the World High; Matt Clements, a forward from 
Bonita High; John Mullinax, a fullback from Katella High, and John Lowell, who 
will be a sophomore goalkeeper and has played for several German clubs. 
</P>
