<P>
DIGEST: MATADOR TRIO MAKE ALL-WEST SOFTBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge softball players Amy Windmiller, Shannon Jones and Tamara 
Ivie were named to the All-Western regional team. 
</P>
<P>
 Windmiller went 22-2 with an 0.30 earned-run average and five no-hitters. 
</P>
<P>
 Third baseman Jones hit .438 with 11 home runs and 47 runs batted in. Utility 
player Ivie hit .420 with four homers and 38 RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Right-hander Heather Meyer of Antelope Valley College was named pitcher of the 
year on the all-state softball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Meyer was joined on the first team by Antelope Valley freshman catcher Donna 
Villa and freshman first baseman Jody Snelling. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark College swept the Western Athletic Conference awards, with Marcie 
James named pitcher of the year, Wendy Baertschiger player of the year and De 
Dow coach of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Other Raiders on the All-WSC team are pitcher Jana Kovar, catcher Marie 
Goulette, first baseman Jennifer Edwards and outfielder Holly Bennett. 
</P>
<P>
 Also named were Canyons pitcher Marianne Winchester, infielder Jamie Dean and 
outfielder Kasey Miller; Ventura outfielder Christine Garcia and Pierce utility 
player Mandy Villasenor. College Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 Mission College's Ray Rivera was selected most valuable player and John 
Klitsner was named coach of the year in the Southern California Athletic 
Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Rivera was 12-3 with a 2.78 ERA, helping the Free Spirit (26-17) to the 
conference title. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission third baseman Dave Valdez, shortstop Erik Lazerus, outfielders Gary 
Matthews and Dereck Ornelas, utilityman Rob Walley and designated hitter 
Francisco Flores also made the team. 
