<P>
 House OKs Credit Card Payment of Taxes: Taxpayers confronted with a bill from 
the Internal Revenue Service may eventually be able to say, "Charge it!" 
Wide-ranging tax legislation approved by the House would authorize the IRS to 
collect payments by credit card, in addition to the checks and money orders now 
accepted. If it happens, it would be part of the IRS plan to have far more 
taxpayers paying and filing by telephone and computer by the turn of the 
century.The legislation, approved on a voice vote, allows the IRS to negotiate 
arrangements with credit card issuers, includes provisions for resolving 
billing disputes and prohibits credit card companies from using customers' tax 
information for marketing. Senate approval is also required. 
</P>
