entirety."In addition, the panel said Gutfreund must pay $96,000 in forum fees. 
Gutfreund, toppled in the wake of Salomon's August, 1991, U.S. Treasury bond 
scandal, sought "to recover compensation, benefits, other damages, interest, 
costs and attorneys' fees." Gutfreund and his lawyers were not immediately 
available for comment. 
