<P>
EXECUTIVE TRAVEL / SPOTLIGHT ON TAIWAN; RESOURCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Researched by ADAM S. BAUMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some useful addresses, phone numbers and publications for doing business in 
Taiwan: 
</P>
<P>
 OFFICIAL FOREIGN OFFICES The Coordination Council can answer questions about 
visa requirements and offer advice on business and trade issues. 
</P>
<P>
 Coordination Council for North American Affairs 4201 Wisconsin Ave. N.W. 
Washington , D.C. 20016 (202) 895-1800 The local office of the Coordination 
Council can assist with common questions; other questions may be referred to 
the Washington office.An Information Division official can provide basic 
information about doing business in Taiwan. 
</P>
<P>
 Coordination Council 900 N. Western Ave. Los Angeles, CA 90029 (213) 461-3665 
The trade specialist in the Commercial Division can provide highly detailed 
information about industrial and investment opportunities in Taiwan. 
</P>
<P>
 Coordination Council, Commercial Division 3660 Wilshire Blvd., Suite 918 Los 
Angeles, CA 90010 (213) 380-3644 There is no U.S. Embassy in Taiwan. Unofficial 
relations with Taiwan are conducted through the American Institute. 
</P>
<P>
 American Institute No. 7 Lane 134 Hsin Yi Road , Section 3 Taipei, Taiwan 
(886-2) 709-2000 , ext. 2306 After-hours emergency number: (886-2) 709-2013 
TRADE CONTACTS 
</P>
<P>
 These agencies can assist businesses or offer locations and special 
incentives. 
</P>
<P>
 American Chamber of Commerce 96 Chungshan Road Room 1012, Section 2 Taipei 
(886-2) 581-7089 Fax: (886-2) 542-3376  
</P>
<P>
 Board of Foreign Trade 1 Hukou St . Taipei (886-2) 321-0561 Fax: (886-2) 
351-3603  
</P>
<P>
 China External Trade Development Council 333 Keelung Road 4th Floor, Section 1 
Taipei (886-2) 725-5200 Fax: (886-2) 757-6653  
</P>
<P>
 Ministry of Economic Affairs, Industrial Development and Investment Center 4 
Chung Hsiao W. Road 19th Floor, Section 1 Taipei (886-2) 389-2111 Fax: (886-2) 
382-0497  
</P>
<P>
 ROC-USA Economic Council 390 Fu Hsin Road S. 13th Floor, Section 1 Taipei 
(886-2) 705-3102 Fax: (886-2) 702-9113  
</P>
<P>
 Sources: Europa Publications; Taipei Coordination Council; U.S. State 
Department 
</P>
