escrow on 34 1/2 acres of land in Los Angeles County where it plans to build 
116 single-family houses. 
</P>
<P>
 The homes, to be built in the Rowland Heights area, are to feature French 
Normandy-style architecture and have as many as five bedrooms.Prices will be in 
the low $300,000s. 
</P>
