POLICE INVESTIGATING FORGERY CASE FIND BODY BURIED IN MONTCLAIR YARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police investigating a suspected check forgery case Wednesday found a corpse 
in a Montclair back yard and said it could be tied to the disappearance six 
months ago of a 68-year-old man. 
</P>
<P>
 Montclair police Lt. Kevin Piper said the decomposing body was found by 
detectives who were looking into suspicious checks that had been cashed in the 
name of John Sullivan, a Montclair man who lives in the 9800 block of Saratoga 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Piper said detectives found the house empty, but investigation prompted them 
to excavate the back yard, where they found the remains of a dog and a male 
corpse. 
</P>
<P>
 Sullivan's two adult sons also live in the house, Piper said. The 
investigation is continuing, he said. 
</P>
