<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHYSIOC WILL REPLACE STARR ON RAM BROADCASTS -- JOINED BY JONES, SNOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Steve Physioc, a Bay Area free-lance play-by-play announcer, will replace Bob 
Starr and will be joined by Hall of Fame member Deacon Jones on Ram radio 
broadcasts next season, The Times has learned. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack Snow will return as a commentator, making it a three-man team. 
</P>
<P>
 KMPC will continue as the Ram flagship station. 
</P>
<P>
 The hiring of Physioc and Jones is part of a new one-year deal among the Rams, 
Niederlander Sports Marketing, which also owns the radio rights to the Raiders, 
and KMPC, now owned by Capital Cities. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
