COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; CHICANO MUSIC AWARDS SET FOR CIVIC AUDITORIUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The sixth annual Chicano Music Awards will return to the Pasadena Civic 
Auditorium on Saturday to raise funds for the Quetzalcoatl Memorial 
Scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
 The awards show is sponsored by Sancho, deejay of the "Sancho Show" on 
Pasadena City College's radio station, KPCC. 
</P>
<P>
 The show will feature a broad range of Chicano music -- from Latin jazz to 
mariachis -- and aims to top last year's nearly $70,000 raised for the 
scholarship fund. Scholarships are given to Chicano students with a proven 
academic record and a commitment to serve their communities after college, the 
station said. 
