<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: PACOIMA; WOMAN, GIRL 
KILLED BY HIT-AND-RUN DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A woman and a young girl were struck and killed by a hit-and-run driver 
Wednesday in the intersection of Montague Street and Laurel Canyon Boulevard in 
Pacoima, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified victims were described as a Latina in her 30s and a girl 
about 12, said Frank Zdroy of the Los Angeles Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Both victims were pronounced dead at the scene, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators believe the car was a red Mustang. Red paint chips and pieces of 
a broken headlight were found at the scene, Zdroy said, and there was evidence 
that the car's left front section and a headlight were damaged in the 
collision. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were searching for the motorist late Wednesday night, Zdroy said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
