<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHILANTHROPY: LOYOLA GETS GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola Marymount University has received a $10-million foundation grant to 
build an underground parking structure, a playing field and additional student 
housing on 27.5 acres of land next to the university's main Westchester campus. 
</P>
<P>
 The grant was made by the Thomas and Dorothy Leavey Foundation of Los Angeles. 
A $2-million donation from the foundation in 1982 allowed the university to 
purchase land for the expansion project. The property is between Lincoln 
Boulevard and the western edge of the main campus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
