<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; RADIO: 'WHICH WAY, L.A.?' WINS AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The KCRW radio show "Which Way, L.A.?" has won the Radio-Television News 
Directors Assn.'s 1994 regional award for best radio series produced by a small 
staff. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, hosted by former local television anchor Warren Olney, won in the 
Arizona, California and Nevada region. Regional winners are automatically 
entered in the national competition for the association's Edward R. Murrow 
Awards, to be announced in Los Angeles on Oct. 12. 
</P>
<P>
 "Which Way, L.A.?," started two years in response to the riots, uses a 
talk-show format to address a variety of issues facing Southern California. The 
one-hour program is broadcast Monday through Friday at 1 p.m. and rebroadcast 
at 7 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
