<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; ADOPT A PET DAY AT O.C. ANIMAL SHELTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To help observe Be Kind to Animals Month and to celebrate the grand reopening 
of the Orange County Animal Shelter, the county facility will hold Adopt a Pet 
Day on Saturday . 
</P>
<P>
 Free spaying and neutering will be available for any pet adopted at the 
shelter that day. 
</P>
<P>
 Exhibits from animal care organizations, a dog show, photo and poster contest 
also will highlight the event from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. at the shelter, 531 The 
City Drive in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 County officials say they want to let the public know about the many animals 
up for adoption at the shelter and educate people about pet care. 
</P>
<P>
 Free animal care products will be available and the Animal Assistance League 
of Orange County will donate certificates good for free spaying and neutering 
of any animal adopted on Saturday . 
</P>
<P>
 The event will be the first opportunity for the county facility to show off 
its recently completed renovations, including a newly designed main entrance 
and parking lot. 
</P>
<P>
 Trained police dogs and canines associated with the Santa Ana Valley Kennel 
club will give demonstrations. County officials will also have a pet photo 
contest and a children's Be Kind To Animals poster contest. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 935-6943. 
</P>
</TEXT>
