<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HUNTINGTON PARK: FORMER OFFICIAL GETS JAIL FOR EMBEZZLEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former city official Rudolfo E. Munoz has been sentenced to 90 days in County 
Jail and ordered to repay $24,000 he embezzled from the city in 1989 and 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 Munoz, 31, was the city's assistant director of development when he pocketed 
more than $24,000 in in-lieu parking fees from developers Manouchehr and Amir 
Masjedi, who were constructing a building at 6363 Pacific Blvd., said Efrem M. 
Grail, deputy district attorney with the Special Investigations Unit. 
</P>
<P>
 Munoz pleaded guilty in October to one felony count of embezzlement, 
falsification and misappropriation of accounts by a public officer. 
</P>
